attack types are introduced.

25
00:02:03,090 --> 00:02:05,890
Like many other networks
also the smart grid

26
00:02:05,890 --> 00:02:08,490
suffers from denial of service attacks.

27
00:02:09,695 --> 00:02:13,640
These attacks can target different
layers of the smart grid network

28
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:14,660
in different ways.

29
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:21,450
In the physical layer, channel jamming
is the most common attack type,

30
00:02:21,450 --> 00:02:23,390
especially in wireless communication.

31
00:02:24,730 --> 00:02:29,268
Since it's easier for an attacker to
intercept wireless communication channels

32
00:02:29,268 --> 00:02:31,410
than authenticated networks.

33
00:02:33,810 --> 00:02:38,672
In the media access control or
a MAC layer, by spoofing MAC parameters,

34
00:02:38,672 --> 00:02:42,339
an attacker has a better chance
to access the network in

35
00:02:42,339 --> 00:02:47,205
order to reduce the performance of
shared communication channels, and

36
00:02:47,205 --> 00:02:50,979
compromise availability and
integrity of the system.

37
00:02:52,893 --> 00:02:57,383
In the network and
the transport layers, denial-of-service

38
00:02:57,383 --> 00:03:02,131
attacks can reduce the end-to-end
communication performance.

39
00:03:03,290 --> 00:03:08,740
Especially worm propagation and
traffic flooding in these layers

40
00:03:08,740 --> 00:03:13,480
can considerably reduce the communication
speed, and thereby the overall

41
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:18,540
performance of the smart grid.

42
00:03:18,540 --> 00:03:24,750
In the application layer, an attacker
targets machine's resources, such as CPU

43
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:31,130
or I/O bandwidth by exhausting resources
of smart devices and computer systems.

44
00:03:33,260 --> 00:03:36,220
In a smart grid, majority of computing and

45
00:03:36,220 --> 00:03:40,630
communication devices are resource
constrained, and therefore,

46
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:44,730
this kind of attack is very serious and
threatening for a smart grid.

47
00:03:48,430 --> 00:03:54,670
In addition to denial of service attacks,
which may target the availability,

48
00:03:54,670 --> 00:03:59,300
smart grids are also vulnerable
to some other attack types

49
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:04,610
which target integrity and confidentiality
of the customer's information.

50
00:04:04,610 --> 00:04:09,364
For example, usage and pricing
information and also power system values,

51
00:04:09,364 --> 00:04:11,006
such as device readings.

52
00:04:13,468 --> 00:04:16,307
Such attacks are more complicated and

53
00:04:16,307 --> 00:04:20,040
less brute force than
denial of service attacks.

54
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:24,759
The risks of integrity attacks
are very high and real.

55
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:32,800
False data injection is an example
of an integrity attack,

56
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,580
which influences both users and suppliers.

57
00:04:36,730 --> 00:04:40,710
In this type of attack the attacker
compromises a number of

58
00:04:40,710 --> 00:04:43,839
measuring devices to
inject false information.

59
00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:50,190
This attack can have a long-term and
heavy impact on smart grid systems,

60
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:53,920
resulting in a significant
financial loss for the suppliers.

61
00:04:56,460 --> 00:05:01,410
On the other hand, attacks which target
the confidentiality of information

62
00:05:01,410 --> 00:05:05,180
are not meant to modify the information,
but

63
00:05:05,180 --> 00:05:07,540
to gain knowledge about
sensitive information.

64
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:12,850
Eavesdropping is one of the main
attack types in this category.

65
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:18,570
Targeted information is typically
a customer's account number or

66
00:05:18,570 --> 00:05:19,780
electricity usage.

67
00:05:22,460 --> 00:05:27,300
Data security and
privacy are a top concern in smart grids.

68
00:05:28,790 --> 00:05:32,930
Utilization of cloud computing for
data storage and

69
00:05:32,930 --> 00:05:36,485
processing has caused even
more problems for smart grids.

70
00:05:36,485 --> 00:05:42,175
Indeed, the wide range and large amount
of data originating from multiple

71
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:48,420
sources makes it challenging to guarantee
data security and privacy in the grid.

72
00:05:49,820 --> 00:05:55,630
Especially if data, either public or
private, has multiple owners.

73
00:05:55,630 --> 00:06:00,010
It is more probable that personally
identifiable information

74
00:06:00,010 --> 00:06:04,210
